8: **Day Number Headers** (Critical)\n- Column A: \"NO\" (Item Number)\n- Column B: \"검사 항목\" (Inspection Item)\n- Column G: \"검사 기준\" (Check Standard)\n- Column L: \"검사 결과\" (Check Result)\n- Column O: \"시간\" (Time/Shift)\n- **Columns Q, S, U, W, Y, AA, AC, AE, AG, AI, AK, AM, AO, AQ, AS, AU, AW, AY, BA, BC, BE, BG, BI, BK, BM, BO, BQ, BS, BU, BW, BY**\n  - These contain: **Day 1, Day 2, Day 3, ... Day 31**\n  - Pattern: Every other column starting at Q\n\n#### Row 19: **Shift Headers** (Critical)\n- All columns Q-BY contain: \"아침\" (Morning), \"점심\" (Noon), \"저녁\" (Evening) repeated\n- These represent sub-columns for each day's data entry\n\n### 2.2 Data Area (Rows 20-65)\n\n**15 Inspection Items**, each spanning **3 rows**\n\n| Item # | Rows | Description | Check Standard | Frequency |\n|--------|------|-------------|-----------------|-----------|\n| 1 | 20-22 | AIR 압송 및 압력 확인 | 4~6 kgf/cm², 0.4~0.6Mpa | 1회/SHIFT |\n| 2 | 23-25 | 습기/이물 압송 확인 | 습기 없을 것 | 당번 |\n| 3 | 26-28 | 클러치/스핀들 구동 확인 | 구동 이상 없을 것 | 당번 |\n| 4 | 29-31 | 로봇암 구동 확인 | 구동상태 정상 여부 확인 | 당번 |\n| 5 | 32-34 | F/PROOF 용접 외관 확인 | 용접 외 부드러운지 / 비드 거칠지 않을 것 | 당번 |\n| 6 | 35-37 | 용접클리닝 및 정정작업 확인 | 청소됨 여부 / 2시간/1회 | 당번 |\n| 7 | 39-41 | 비드면 치수 확인 및 정정 | 9~11mm | 당번 |\n| 8 | 42-44 | 비드부 외관 확인 | 비드부 색상 등 이상 없을 것 | 당번 |\n| 9 | 45-47 | 모서 코너 점수 확인 | 용접 이상/진동/누수 없을 것 | 당번 |\n| 10 | 48-50 | 전류 (LH/RH) | 125~165 A | 당번 |\n| 11 | 51-53 | 전압 (LH/RH) | 17~23 V | 당번 |\n| 12 | 54-56 | GAS (LH/RH) | 16~20 L/min | 당번 |\n| 13 | 57-59 | WIRE 공급&전선 조임 매일점검 | 1회 / 200타 작업(점검내용) | 당번 |\n| 14 | 60-62 | 롤러셋 메정 | 1회 /50타 작업(점검내용) | 당번 |\n| 15 | 63-65 | 월 교환 및 청청확인 | 성능 저하여부 확인 교환 & 클린확인 | 1회/월 |\n\n**Each item row contains:**\n- Column A: Item number (1-15)\n- Column B: Item description (some multi-line)\n- Column G: Check standard/criteria (spec values or descriptions)\n- Column L: Check result notation or schedule\n- Column O: Frequency/Timing (당번=per shift, 1회/SHIFT=once per shift, etc.)\n- Columns Q onwards: Data entry cells for each day\n\n### 2.3 Footer Area (Rows 66-76)\n\n| Row | Content | Purpose |\n|-----|---------|---------|\n| 66 | 결과 ○합격 : O ×불합격 : X 기타:따로기입 | Legend explaining marks |\n| 66 | 검사 기준 (SIGN) | Signature space for inspector |\n| 67 | (empty) | |\n| 68 | 기술 감독 (SIGN) | Signature space for supervisor |\n| 69 | 품질 감독 (SIGN) | Signature space for quality manager |\n| 70-76 | (empty/comments) | Additional notes area |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Column Structure Detailed\n\n### Column Groups\n\n| Columns | Purpose | Width |\n|---------|---------|-------|\n| A | Item number | Narrow |\n| B | Item description | Wide |\n| C | (metadata/blank) | |\n| D-F | (blank) | |\n| G | Check standard/criterion | Wide |\n| H-K | (blank) | |\n| L | Check result/schedule | Medium |\n| M-N | (blank) | |\n| O | Frequency/Timing | Narrow |\n| P | (blank/separator) | |\n| Q-BY | **31 Days of Data** | See below |\n\n### Day Columns (Q-BY)\n\nEach day occupies **2 adjacent columns**:\n\n```\nDay 1:  Q (header) + R (shifts)\nDay 2:  S (header) + T (shifts)\nDay 3:  U (header) + V (shifts)\nDay 4:  W (header) + X (shifts)\nDay 5:  Y (header) + Z (shifts)\nDay 6:  AA (header) + AB (shifts)\nDay 7:  AC (header) + AD (shifts)\nDay 8:  AE (header) + AF (shifts)\nDay 9:  AG (header) + AH (shifts)\nDay 10: AI (header) + AJ (shifts)\nDay 11: AK (header) + AL (shifts)\nDay 12: AM (header) + AN (shifts)\nDay 13: AO (header) + AP (shifts)\nDay 14: AQ (header) + AR (shifts)\nDay 15: AS (header) + AT (shifts)\nDay 16: AU (header) + AV (shifts)\nDay 17: AW (header) + AX (shifts)\nDay 18: AY (header) + AZ (shifts)\nDay 19: BA (header) + BB (shifts)\nDay 20: BC (header) + BD (shifts)\nDay 21: BE (header) + BF (shifts)\nDay 22: BG (header) + BH (shifts)\nDay 23: BI (header) + BJ (shifts)\nDay 24: BK (header) + BL (shifts)\nDay 25: BM (header) + BN (shifts)\nDay 26: BO (header) + BP (shifts)\nDay 27: BQ (header) + BR (shifts)\nDay 28: BS (header) + BT (shifts)\nDay 29: BU (header) + BV (shifts)\nDay 30: BW (header) + BX (shifts)\nDay 31: BY (header) + BZ (shifts)\n```\n\n**Row 18:** Shows day number (1, 2, 3, ... 31) in the header columns (Q, S, U, ...)\n**Row 19:** Shows shift indicators in all columns (아침, 점심, 저녁 repeated)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Control Sheets Structure\n\n### RECL점검 Sheet\n\n**Size:** 89 rows × 79 columns\n**Purpose:** Daily inspection of RECL ASSY assembly\n\n#### Key Sections:\n- **Rows 1-18:** Header with title, equipment info, RECL ASSY number field\n- **Rows 19-20:** Column headers (similar to daily sheets)\n- **Rows 21-38:** 9 RECL inspection items\n\n#### RECL Inspection Items:\n1. AIR 압송\n2. AIR 여과\n3. 정밀센터 구동점검\n4. PC 구동점검\n5. 용접 S/W 점검\n6. 로터 청소 점검\n7. DOT 용접 점검\n8. #20 F/PROOF 구동 점검\n9. #40 무결성검사 경보 점검\n\n- **Rows 41-45:** Legend and signature area (합격/불합격, signature fields)\n- **Columns:** Same day column structure as daily sheets (Q-BY for Days 1-31)\n\n### 용접기(DL3) & 용접기(YB) Sheets\n\n**Size:** 69 rows × 78 columns each\n**Purpose:** Equipment-specific daily check for DL3 and YB welding machines\n\n#### Structure:\n- Very similar to daily sheets\n- Title indicates equipment model (DL3 or YB)\n- Typically 10-12 equipment-specific inspection items\n- Same day column layout (Q-BY for Days 1-31)\n- Signature/footer area at rows 60+\n\n---\n\n## 5. Cell Data Types & Formatting\n\n### Cell Contents\n\n| Type | Example | Usage |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| Text | \"AIR 압송 및 압력 확인\" | Item descriptions |\n| Numbers | 1, 2, 3...31 | Day numbers |\n| Single Character | ○ | Pass mark |\n| Single Character | × | Fail mark |\n| Blank | (empty) | Empty data entry cells |\n| Multi-line text | \"기술\\n감독\" | Wrapped text in narrow columns |\n| Numeric ranges | \"4~6 kgf/cm²\" | Check standards |\n| Time labels | \"아침\", \"점심\", \"저녁\" | Shift indicators |\n\n### Merged Cells\n\n**Heavily merged** - approximately **1100+ merged cells** per sheet\n\nCommon merge patterns:\n- Multi-row item descriptions (rows 20-22, 23-25, etc.)\n- Day headers spanning multiple rows\n- Title area cells\n- Signature area cells\n\n**Example:** Row 20 (Item 1) merged across columns to provide space for item details\n\n---\n\n## 6. Data Entry Layout\n\n### Example: Item 1, Days 1-3\n\n```\nRow 18:  Q:\"1\"      S:\"2\"      U:\"3\"      (day numbers)\nRow 19:  Q:\"아침\"   R:\"점심\"   S:\"저녁\"   (shift indicators)\nRow 20:  Q:[  ]     R:[  ]     S:[  ]     (entry cells for each shift)\nRow 21:  Q:[  ]     R:[  ]     S:[  ]     (continuation)\nRow 22:  Q:[  ]     R:[  ]     S:[  ]     (continuation)\n```\n\nEach entry cell can contain:\n- ○ (pass)\n- × (fail)\n- Text notes\n- Numeric values (for current, voltage, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Observations\n\n### 1. **Horizontal Day Layout**\n- Days are arranged **horizontally across columns** (Q-BY)\n- Not vertically (no separate sheets per day needed for data)\n- Allows single-page printing per item inspection\n\n### 2. **Merged Cell Complexity**\n- Extensive merging (1000+) makes programmatic access challenging\n- Requires careful cell reference handling\n- Visual formatting heavily relied upon\n\n### 3. **Multi-row Items**\n- Each inspection item spans 3 rows\n- First row: main description\n- Second & third rows: standards, notes, signature spaces\n\n### 4. **Shift Tracking**\n- Three shifts per day: 아침(Morning), 점심(Noon), 저녁(Evening)\n- Each shift has own column within day's 2-column block\n\n### 5. **Pass/Fail Marking System**\n- ○ = Pass (합격)\n- × = Fail (불합격)\n- No checkboxes; manual entry expected\n\n### 6. **Equipment Segregation**\n- Main daily sheet (15 items)\n- RECL ASSY sheet (9 items)\n- Two equipment-specific sheets (DL3, YB)\n- Allows separate tracking for different equipment lines\n\n---\n\n## 8. Typical Data Entry Flow\n\n1. **At start of month:** Select Day 1 sheet\n2. **For each inspection item (1-15):**\n   - Read standards from Column G\n   - Perform check\n   - Enter result in appropriate day's data cell\n3. **For each shift:** Enter marks in corresponding shift column (아침/점심/저녁)\n4. **Daily:** Repeat for all 31 days\n5. **At month end:** Collect signatures in footer area\n\n---\n\n## 9. File Path References\n\n- **Full Path:** `C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\WELD_MONITOR3_IAM\\요청\\241220 설비,용접조건일상체크시트(최종).xlsx`\n- **Sheet Names:** Encoded in Korean (UTF-8)\n- **Access Method:** Via openpyxl (Python) or Excel (direct)\n\n---\n\n## 10. Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **File Type** | Excel Workbook (.xlsx) |\n| **Total Sheets** | 35 |\n| **Control Sheets** | 3 (RECL점검, DL3, YB) |\n| **Daily Sheets** | 32 (Days 1-31, plus extra) |\n| **Rows per daily sheet** | 76 |\n| **Columns per daily sheet** | 78 (A-BZ) |\n| **Daily Inspection Items** | 15 |\n| **Days Tracked** | 31 (monthly) |\n| **Shifts per Day** | 3 (Morning, Noon, Evening) |\n| **Entry Type** | Manual marks (○/×) |\n| **Merged Cells** | ~1100+ per sheet |\n| **Data Structure** | Horizontal (columns = days) |\n\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":162,"cache_read_input_tokens":50726,"output_tokens":4355,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":162},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYxuv5PzDuU6PrvTy2CNe","type":"assistant","uuid":"8b5d229e-f673-4fa0-b153-b24e246da128","timestamp":"2026-03-12T09:01:31.913Z","userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop","sessionId":"9506a718-9cf9-4c58-a7d8-97e986f31409","version":"2.1.74","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"modular-skipping-elephant"}
